<item>
            <title>[AMQ-1858] Integer overflow in default settings</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/AMQ-1858</link>
                <project id="12311210" key="AMQ">ActiveMQ Classic</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;From BrokerService, line 711-2:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;systemUsage.getTempUsage().setLimit(1024 * 1024 * 1024 * 100); // 10 Gb&lt;br/&gt;
systemUsage.getStoreUsage().setLimit(1024 * 1024 * 1024 * 100); // 100 GB&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The expression 1024 * 1024 * 1024 * 100 overflows int, so the above lines actually correspond to setLimit(0).&lt;br/&gt;
Easy fix is to make one of the multipliers a long, for example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1024L * 1024 * 1024 * 100&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Other places may have the same problem, but I did not look for all places.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
